# [[1]] parcequ'on regarde que un bassin, on peut aller un cran plus bas dans "l(indentation des listes)"
data <-  get_simu_appli_grd(parent_dir = dir_appli, project_dir = dir_project, variantes = variantes, bassins = bassin, withdraw_optim = TRUE)[[1]]

date_min <- lapply(data[[1]], function(variant){
  return(variant$ts$Date[1] )
})
date_max<- lapply(data[[1]], function(variant){
  return(variant$ts$Date[length(variant$ts$Date)] )
})

date_min <- do.call(max, date_min)
date_max <- do.call(min, date_max)

data <- lapply(data, function(sub_catch, date_min, date_max){
  sub_catch <- lapply(sub_catch, function(variant, date_min, date_max){
    variant$ts <- subset(variant$ts, Date >= date_min)
    variant$ts <- subset(variant$ts, Date <= date_max)
    return(variant)
  }, date_min = date_min, date_max = date_max)
  return(sub_catch)
}, date_min = date_min, date_max = date_max)

  })

for(i in 1:length(data[[1]])){
  
    cat("##", names(data[[1]])[i], '<br>', '\n')
  
  if(!grepl("CREST", names(data[[1]])[i])){
    data_with_params <- add_calibration_parameters(data[[1]][[i]], all_param = FALSE)
    cali_params <- data_with_params$parameters
    print(knitr::kable(cali_params, format="html", caption = paste0("parameters for ",names(data[[1]])[i] ), row.names = FALSE) %>%
            kable_styling(bootstrap_options = "striped", full_width = F, position = "center"))
    
    cat('\n', '<br>', '\n\n')
    
  }else{
    cali_params <- get_cali_res_crest(data[[1]][[i]])
    print(knitr::kable(cali_params, format="html", caption = paste0("parameters for ",names(data[[1]])[i] ), row.names = FALSE) %>%
            kable_styling(bootstrap_options = "striped", full_width = F, position = "center"))
  }
  
  write.table(x = cali_params, file =  file.path(export_path, paste0("cali_params_", names(data[[1]])[i],".csv")), 
                         append = FALSE, 
                         quote = FALSE, 
                         sep = ";", 
                         col.names = TRUE, 
                         row.names = FALSE)
}

options(default.stringsAsFactors = FALSE)

bilan_brut <- build_bilan(data, "mean", digits = 5)
bilan_brut <- lapply(bilan_brut, function(gauge) {
  names_simu <- names(gauge)
  gauge <- do.call(rbind, gauge)
  gauge <- cbind("simu" = names_simu, gauge)
  return(gauge)})

names_gauge <- character()
k=0
for(i in 1:length(bilan_brut)){
  for(j in 1:nrow(bilan_brut[[i]])){
   k=k+1
   names_gauge[k] <- names(bilan_brut)[i]
  }
}
bilan_brut <- do.call(rbind, bilan_brut)
bilan_brut <- cbind("gauge" = names_gauge, bilan_brut)


p_obs <- q_obs <-q_sim <- bilan_brut

p_obs <- cbind("var" = "p_obs", p_obs[,c("gauge", "simu", "temps_jours", "p_obs")]) 
q_obs <- cbind("var" = "q_obs", q_obs[,c("gauge", "simu", "temps_jours", "q_obs")]) 
q_sim <- cbind("var" = "q_sim", q_sim[,c("gauge", "simu", "temps_jours", "q_sim")])
colnames(p_obs) <- colnames(q_obs) <- colnames(q_sim) <- c("var", "gauge", "simu", "temps_jours", "value")

bilan <- rbind(p_obs, q_obs)
bilan <- rbind(bilan, q_sim)
bilan <- as.data.frame(bilan, stringsAsFactors=FALSE)
bilan$value <- as.numeric(bilan$value)


p <- list()
unique_gauge <- as.character(unique(bilan$gauge))
 for(i in 1:length(unique_gauge)){
  new_bilan <- subset(bilan, bilan$gauge == unique_gauge[i])
 p[[i]] <-  ggplot(data=new_bilan, aes(x=var, y=value, fill=simu)) +
  geom_bar(stat="identity", position=position_dodge()) +
  labs(title= paste0(unique_gauge[i]),
                      y="mean (mm/h)")+
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))
 }
do.call("grid.arrange", c(p, ncol=2))

7 Perfs

names_gauge <- names(data)

for(i in 1:length(names_gauge)){
    cat("##", names_gauge[i], '<br>', '\n')
  
  perf <- list()
  for(j in 1:length(data[[names_gauge[i]]])){
    GRD_df <- data[[names_gauge[i]]][[j]]$ts
    if(length(which(!is.na(GRD_df[,"q_obs"])) != 0 )){
      perf[[j]] <- t(hydroGOF::gof(obs = GRD_df[,"q_obs"], sim = GRD_df[,"q_sim"], na.rm = TRUE))
    }else{
      perf[[j]] <- c("ME" = NA,  "MAE"= NA, "MSE"= NA, "RMSE"= NA, "NRMSE"= NA, "% PBIAS %"= NA,  "RSR"= NA,  "rSD"= NA, "NSE"= NA, "mNSE"= NA, "rNSE"= NA,    "d"= NA,   "md"= NA,   "rd"= NA,     "cp"= NA,    "r"= NA,   "R2"= NA, "bR2"= NA,  "KGE"= NA,   "VE"= NA)
    }
  }
  
perf <- do.call(rbind, perf)
perf <- cbind("variant" = names(data[[names_gauge[i]]]), perf)
perf <- as.data.frame(perf)
    
print(knitr::kable(perf, format="html", caption = paste0("perforance for", names_gauge[i]), row.names = FALSE) %>%
  kable_styling(bootstrap_options = "striped", full_width = F, position = "center"))

  cat('\n', '<br>', '\n\n')
  
   write.table(x = perf, file =  file.path(export_path, paste0("hydroGOF_perf_", names_gauge[i],".csv")), 
                         append = FALSE, 
                         quote = FALSE, 
                         sep = ";", 
                         col.names = TRUE, 
                         row.names = FALSE)
}

9 Plot of Deviation

multi_deviation_grd_V2 <- function(data_g, name_gauge, save_dir, date_min, 
                                   date_max, plot_size, is.png, warmup_line){
  
  
  date_brut <- data_g[[1]]$ts$Date
  if(missing(date_min)) date_min <- date_brut[1]
  if(missing(date_max)) date_max <-date_brut[length(date_brut)]
  if(missing(plot_size)) plot_size <- c("x" = 480, "y" = 380)
  if(missing(is.png)) is.png  <- TRUE
  if(missing(warmup_line)) warmup_line <- FALSE
  
  
  # prepare data for plot ----
  data <- lapply(data_g, function(grd_df, date_max){
    grd_df <- grd_df$ts
    return(subset(grd_df, Date <=date_max))}, date_max = date_max)
  
  data <- lapply(data_g, function(grd_df, date_max){
    grd_df <- grd_df$ts
    return(subset(grd_df, Date >=date_min))}, date_max = date_min)
  
  # data to plot 
  dates <- data[[1]]$Date
  obs_flow <- data[[1]]$q_obs
  rain <- data[[1]]$q_sim
  
  sim_flow <- lapply(data, function(grd_df){
     vals <- abs((grd_df$q_obs - grd_df$q_sim)/grd_df$q_obs)
     id <- which(is.na(vals))
    vals[id] <- 0
    vals <- cumsum(vals)
    vals[i] <- NA
    return(vals)
    
    })
  sim_flow <- do.call(cbind, sim_flow)
  
  # parameters for the plot
  # ylim axis
  max_flow <- max(sim_flow, na.rm = TRUE)
  # name legend
  legende <- c("precip", paste0("q sim ", colnames(sim_flow)))
  # colors for legend and plot
  col_legend <- c("blue", "red", "black", "orange", "purple", "green", "grey")
  
  
  # prepare the save the plot ----
  # plot rainfall -----
  ## Plot rainfall first
  par(xaxs="i", yaxs="i", mar=c(5,5,5,5))
  plot(dates, rain, type="h", ylim=c(max(na.omit(rain)),0),
       axes=FALSE, xlab=NA, ylab=NA,
       lwd=0.1, lend="square", col = col_legend[1])
  axis(4)
  mtext("Rainfall (mm)", side=4, line=3)
  
  # plot q sim ----     

    par(new=TRUE)
    plot(dates, sim_flow[,1],  ylim=c(0,1.2*max_flow), type="l", lwd=1, xlab=NA, ylab=NA, col = col_legend[2])

  for(i in 2:ncol(sim_flow)){
    par(new=TRUE)
    lines(dates, sim_flow[,i], type="l", lwd=1,  col = col_legend[1+i])
  }
  
  
  # add warmup bar ----
  if(warmup_line){
    abline(v = YYYYMMDDHHMM_to_date(data_g[[1]]$task$date$start_optim), col = "black", lwd = 3, lty = 2) #
    text( x= YYYYMMDDHHMM_to_date(data_g[[1]]$task$date$start_optim) + 20000000, y= max(max_flow), labels = "  Fin Chauffe", col = "black", pos = 3)
  }
  
  # add legend and title ----      
  legend(x = dates[1], y = mean(c(max_flow, mean(sim_flow[,1], na.rm = TRUE))), legend=legende,
         col=col_legend, lty=c(1, 1, 1), cex=0.8)
    
  graphics::title(main = paste0("Deviation for multiple simuations of ", name_gauge), 
                  xlab = "Dates", ylab = "Deviation sum(Qobs(i)-Qsim(i)/Qobs(i)) ")
}



for (i in 1:length(data)){
  cat("##", names(data)[i], '<br>', '\n')
  
   try(multi_deviation_grd_V2(data_g = data[[i]], 
                           name_gauge = names(data)[i],
                           warmup_line = FALSE))
  
  cat('\n', '<br>', '\n\n')
}
